Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.66,0:00:03.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The contents of the heart are a mystery...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.25,0:00:05.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like the sparkling stars and snow around us.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.29,0:00:06.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the conclusion of the story of the armored warrior...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.96,0:00:08.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The sad feelings behind the legend come to light!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.17,0:00:10.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seeing through to the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.84,0:00:12.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I look like a child, but have the intellect of an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.46,0:00:14.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.43,0:01:48.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unable to go to the hot springs due to snowfall...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.06,0:01:50.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We were invited to stay at the Daimon residence.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.65,0:01:53.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, the next morning...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.48,0:01:56.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In a room separated from the rest of the residence...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.23,0:01:58.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The body of Daimon Genichiro, the head of the family, was found.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.20,0:02:01.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, in the audio room...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.78,0:02:06.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,e found the deceased body of Kazuki, the eldest son, dressed in the cursed armor.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.37,0:02:12.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Fearful Legend of the Snowy Night:
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.42,0:02:13.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Part 2!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.76,0:02:25.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The pattern of this wound mirrors the one found on Genichiro.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.06,0:02:28.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Most likely, that katana was used as the weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.02,0:02:33.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just like I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.02,0:02:35.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just like I thought, this is Hidetomo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}'s curse.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.19,0:02:44.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That armor called forth Hidetomo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}'s soul, killed my husband for his transgressions...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.53,0:02:47.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then proceeded to kill my precious Kazuki!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.79,0:02:52.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Afterwards, it left the armor on Kazuki to symbolize the curse.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.88,0:02:59.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whether it's a curse or not is still uncertain. However...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.96,0:03:03.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We know that those footprints lead us from the back to the main part of the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.51,0:03:07.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means..
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.43,0:03:09.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did the armored warrior really...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.02,0:03:14.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In any case, let's call the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.19,0:03:21.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Until the police come, I'd like everyone to convene in the living room.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.61,0:03:24.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll go prepare some coffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.62,0:03:27.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now's my chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.08,0:03:27.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.37,0:03:29.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'll get scolded by Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.95,0:03:31.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.66,0:03:34.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hatsuho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, I'll help you too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.63,0:03:36.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.63,0:03:41.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The police are going to be delayed because of the snow.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.46,0:03:42.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.09,0:03:47.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yoshiro, you're the only person left who can protect this house.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.10,0:03:48.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mother..
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.39,0:03:53.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In any case, who would do such a thing to my father and brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.48,0:03:59.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is that stain?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.48,0:04:00.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Blood?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.57,0:04:02.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was it at the last crime scene?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.15,0:04:03.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.57,0:04:05.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's only one plausible explanation.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.95,0:04:09.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazuki went to the separated room and killed Genichiro...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.49,0:04:12.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then returned to the audio room and committed suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.54,0:04:14.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would Kazuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} do such a thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.29,0:04:16.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't there a reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.54,0:04:22.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My brother has always been against Dad's way of doing things, so a fight must have broken out...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.38,0:04:24.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then he killed him in the spur of the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.01,0:04:27.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then it's just like the legend said.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.68,0:04:34.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But didn't Yoshiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} come back just to set things straight with our father?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.19,0:04:36.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you forget that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.60,0:04:40.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On top of that, your story about being a guitarist is a lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.73,0:04:44.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In actuality, you came to take over Daimon Industries, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.57,0:04:50.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With Father and my husband out of the way, you're next in line to take over the company.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.33,0:04:53.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How can you say such things?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.24,0:04:56.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How am I supposed to have gotten to his room in the first place?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.46,0:04:59.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There were no footprints leading out of the main house.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.54,0:05:01.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That goes for Kazuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.67,0:05:08.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true that there are only footprints leading to the main house.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.39,0:05:09.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the curse.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.01,0:05:16.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Late last night, I saw the armored warrior walking to the main house from the separated room.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.77,0:05:19.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mother, you were probably just dreaming.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.15,0:05:21.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This was no dream!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.86,0:05:23.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I am certain that I saw it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.78,0:05:26.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Blocking out the moonlight...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.40,0:05:31.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was the towering figure of that armored warrior.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.58,0:05:40.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Grandma, was that armored warrior holding a katana?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.58,0:05:43.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let me think..
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.51,0:05:49.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't believe I saw him holding a katana...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.13,0:05:52.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I suppose he could've been holding it in his opposite hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.72,0:05:57.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jeez, don't ask such useless things.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.89,0:06:01.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Two things are troubling me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.06,0:06:07.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did the culprit leave the main house and get to Genichiro without leaving any footprints?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.40,0:06:12.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And why did the culprit, dressed in the suit of armor, go to the audio room?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.91,0:06:16.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, I've got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.66,0:06:21.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This conversation is hard to understand and it's boring...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.25,0:06:23.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I'm gonna go play in the snow!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.17,0:06:25.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, stay here!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.67,0:06:28.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How can you think about that at a time like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.47,0:06:29.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.97,0:06:31.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't "wow" me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.76,0:06:34.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jeez..
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.60,0:06:37.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop wandering around all the time!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.39,0:06:38.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.85,0:06:43.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Uncle, my footprints disappeared. I wonder why?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.52,0:06:46.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you blabbering on about now?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.32,0:06:51.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could this be?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.20,0:06:56.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay, here's my chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.75,0:07:02.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The door was locked from the inside...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.67,0:07:05.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The door specifically made for this audio room.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.63,0:07:09.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With no other entrance, it'd be impossible to do something from the outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.42,0:07:12.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All the audio devices were off.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.22,0:07:16.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, the wound is exactly like Genichiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.26,0:07:20.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Most likely, that katana is the weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.85,0:07:24.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why is it near the entrance...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.27,0:07:26.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While everything else is near the body?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.65,0:07:30.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did Kazuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} throw it after stabbing himself?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.65,0:07:32.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, that's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.45,0:07:39.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why is there a blood-covered gash here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.16,0:07:43.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The blood at the top has been wiped off!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.25,0:07:48.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.09,0:07:51.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With this, I've solved the mystery of the locked room.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.64,0:07:59.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just as I thought, there are no bloodstains on this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.97,0:08:01.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who could have done it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.60,0:08:04.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.02,0:08:09.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's barefoot!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.11,0:08:14.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute, the culprit was supposed to have taken the socks as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.28,0:08:17.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it wasn't to make Kazuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} wear them...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.70,0:08:19.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then why were they taken?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.74,0:08:23.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did the culprit have another purpose for them?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.33,0:08:27.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.80,0:08:33.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, I've got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.59,0:08:36.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if that's the case, then they should be hidden somewhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.84,0:08:39.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone, I've completely solved the mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.64,0:08:43.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mystery? Do you mean the lack of footprints?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.93,0:08:45.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That is correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.85,0:08:48.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Most likely, late last night...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.11,0:08:53.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazuki-shi went to the separate house wearing sandals or something...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.57,0:08:57.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And killed Genichiro-shi for some reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.16,0:09:00.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that, Kazuki-shi donned the armor...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.41,0:09:06.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And headed for the main house, carefully walking over his footprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.50,0:09:12.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The weight of the armor cause the second set of footprints to be larger than the first...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.51,0:09:18.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Creating the illusion that there was a sole set of footprints leading from to the main house the separated room.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.01,0:09:19.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.35,0:09:25.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, after returning to the audio room, he locked the door from the inside...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.35,0:09:30.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And committed suicide by slitting his throat.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.65,0:09:32.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-That can't be.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.57,0:09:34.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't believe he would do such a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.16,0:09:45.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just like I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.58,0:09:48.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, if I could just find that thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.34,0:09:55.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.63,0:10:00.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.26,0:10:03.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.97,0:10:05.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.35,0:10:09.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As I thought, these are serial murders using the legend of Hidetomo as a cover!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.56,0:10:13.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the true culprit is that person!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.99,0:10:22.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, I can't believe he would commit suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.70,0:10:26.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's unfortunate, ma'am, but that is the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.17,0:10:31.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,M-Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.67,0:10:36.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Forget everything I just saidâ€”that was just a rouse to make the culprit let their guard down.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.26,0:10:38.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.13,0:10:41.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've only scratched the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.89,0:10:45.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit who killed Genichiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.68,0:10:48.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really did attempt to cover his tracks with the footprint technique I explained earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.85,0:10:56.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But in that case anyone other than Tatsuko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who saw the armor, could have done it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.90,0:10:58.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.45,0:11:04.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then my brother isn't the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.95,0:11:06.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.08,0:11:09.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} did not kill Genichiro-shi.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.83,0:11:10.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moreover..
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.29,0:11:13.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.04,0:11:20.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Most likely, after killing Genichiro-shi, the culprit was splattered with blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.26,0:11:27.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, neither the armor nor Kazuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s clothes have been stained.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.39,0:11:34.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After the culprit killed Genichiro-shi, they came into the audio room and killed Kazuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.90,0:11:36.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But how?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.82,0:11:40.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Recall the katana lying on the floor in the audio room.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.65,0:11:45.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When we first saw it, we jumped to the conclusion that it was used only as the weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.41,0:11:50.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, that katana wasn't just a weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.04,0:11:53.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It had another particularly sneaky purpose...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.87,0:11:57.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To turn the audio room into a locked room.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.75,0:12:03.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After the culprit killed Kazuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, they dressed him in the armor...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.93,0:12:07.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then stabbed the katana into the wall near the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.10,0:12:12.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, with the other end of the katana...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.73,0:12:16.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They rested it upon the door handle...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.86,0:12:22.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Slowly but surely exited the room without letting the katana fall...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.15,0:12:25.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And used the force of the closing door to make the katana bolt the lock.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.95,0:12:30.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With this, the sealed room was complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.91,0:12:36.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They knew that no one would have the strength to open the dead-bolted door.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.50,0:12:41.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And they also knew that trying to break the door down...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.42,0:12:45.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would cause the katana to fall to the floor, leaving the trick would unexposed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.43,0:12:48.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or so the culprit thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.35,0:12:51.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But who in the world did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.60,0:12:58.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before that, we must analyze the significance of this case happening on the anniversary of Hidetomo's death.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.56,0:13:03.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit took advantage of the legend...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.74,0:13:11.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And left those large footprints to make it seem as though the only possible culprit was the armored warrior.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.99,0:13:18.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This fooled us into believing that Kazuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} killed Genichiro-shi and commited suicide shortly thereafter.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.38,0:13:25.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To make this more believable, the culprit purposely directed Tatsuko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.17,0:13:28.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who strongly believed in the legend, to bear witness to the animated suit of armor.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.01,0:13:32.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Being the the anniversary of Hidetomo's death, everyone knew that Tatsuko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.31,0:13:35.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would be praying at the altar at exactly 12:00 AM.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.48,0:13:40.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, isn't it convenient that the armor happened to walk by that spot at that exact time?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.02,0:13:45.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, as a result, the culprit left a clue behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.70,0:13:49.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tatsuko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}..
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.11,0:13:53.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The armored warrior you saw last night wasn't holding a katana, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.58,0:13:55.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, it's as you say.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.70,0:13:58.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually, that's not exactly the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.46,0:14:04.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because of your position, and due to the shadow of the body, you couldn't see it being held in the right hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.63,0:14:07.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words; the culprit is probably left-handed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.09,0:14:11.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.34,0:14:15.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, why would they hold it in their right hand if they're left-handed?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.89,0:14:18.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to draw the katana with the left hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.56,0:14:21.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The sheath must be held in the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.23,0:14:23.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's..
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.98,0:14:26.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Yoshiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is not the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.53,0:14:31.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit is another left-handed person.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.82,0:14:35.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Houjo Hatsuho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, it's you!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.25,0:14:39.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hatsuho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}..
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.79,0:14:42.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're also left-handed, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.00,0:14:47.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you were serving coffee a while ago, you were using your left hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.96,0:14:49.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.59,0:14:53.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But as for how you hold a katana, that doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.97,0:14:58.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, I don't have a reason to want to kill either one of them!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.98,0:15:00.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran..
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.19,0:15:05.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could you please go to Hatsuho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s room and bring me the old photo that's on her dresser?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.90,0:15:07.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,O-Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.99,0:15:12.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have one more question to ask you before Ran returns.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.74,0:15:16.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hatsuko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, when you were in your room earlier...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.24,0:15:20.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You saw Genichiro-shi in the separate room, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.29,0:15:21.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.50,0:15:29.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But think about this carefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.01,0:15:36.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it really possible to tell whether Genichiro-shi had passed away or merely fell over...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.97,0:15:40.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All the way from inside the main house?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.23,0:15:42.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's..
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.44,0:15:45.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was just flustered after having seen Master collapsed on the floor...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.48,0:15:50.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran, place the photo on the table for everyone to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.44,0:15:51.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.11,0:15:56.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take a look at this, Yoshiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.12,0:15:59.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you recognize the person in the picture?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.41,0:16:00.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.54,0:16:03.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hatsuho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, probably with her father.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.37,0:16:05.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.63,0:16:07.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's the one from that article who committed suicide!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.34,0:16:12.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.72,0:16:16.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hatsuho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had the motive to kill both of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.89,0:16:20.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hatsuho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}..
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.81,0:16:23.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You went to the audio room, where Kazuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.23,0:16:28.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Brought him the cup of coffee that he had asked for, which you had already laced with sleeping pills...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.15,0:16:31.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then you went out the back door to go to the separate room.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.40,0:16:39.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Genichiro-shi probably opened the door without a second thought when he heard you outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.87,0:16:44.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was when you killed him, and quickly put on the armor.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.83,0:16:47.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, stepping over your previous footprints, you headed for the main house.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.38,0:16:53.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You took a route that couldn't be seen from Yoshiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s, Kayoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s, or our rooms...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.30,0:17:00.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But your route could be seen from Tatsuko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s room, as well as your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.72,0:17:10.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Most likely, you wrapped white sheets around yourself before you left, in order to blend in with the snow."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.94,0:17:14.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I was searching around the main house...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.86,0:17:17.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I saw something sticking out of the closet.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.20,0:17:20.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was a set of sheets that looked to be hurriedly shoved in.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.03,0:17:22.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All of this..
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.62,0:17:24.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All of this is just your imagination
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.75,0:17:27.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true that my father committed suicide...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.29,0:17:31.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it's true that I changed my name to conceal my past...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.92,0:17:36.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that doesn't come close to proving that I killed anyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.59,0:17:38.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have proof...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.26,0:17:41.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the kitchen stove.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.68,0:17:45.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan found them earlier...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.23,0:17:51.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An old, worn-out parka and the pair of socks that Tatsuko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had left at the feet of the altar.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.19,0:17:52.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But those were in the kitchen!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.82,0:17:54.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How is that incriminating evidence?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.15,0:17:59.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Somebody could have hidden them in the stove to set me up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.74,0:18:03.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyone could have hidden the parka and socks after the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.41,0:18:06.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're the only one who could have done it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.04,0:18:12.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The socks that Tatsuko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} offered disappeared, and weren't found on the corpse.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.92,0:18:17.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If they weren't intended for Kazuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to wear...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.92,0:18:21.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then why did the culprit take them and hide them in the stove?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.05,0:18:24.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hatsuho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}..
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.14,0:18:26.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You injured your left foot, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.85,0:18:35.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You hadn't been tending to it well, which caused the scab to re-open a while ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.23,0:18:39.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you were serving coffee earlier...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.28,0:18:42.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I could see a blood stain on your socks.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.59,0:19:00.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you killed Genichiro-shi, he had dropped a glass bottle...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.47,0:19:05.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And you stepped on one of its shards, injuring your foot.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.77,0:19:10.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you wore the armor's shoes with such a wound, your blood would create a stain.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.60,0:19:19.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To avoid that, you put on the socks that Tatsuko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had offered prior to the armored shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.32,0:19:27.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, on the way back, you hid the socks and parka in the kitchen stove.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.99,0:19:32.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You thought you could leave them there, and dispose of them properly the next day...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.17,0:19:34.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since no one else would be using the kitchen.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.54,0:19:41.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Ran wound up helping you with the coffee, and that opportunity was lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.14,0:19:50.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.14,0:19:51.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's exactly as you said.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.77,0:19:54.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I killed both of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.06,0:19:56.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How... How could you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.44,0:19:59.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You always treat me so kindly.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.32,0:20:06.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My father, who owned his own company, cherished human relations over cruel business deals.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.78,0:20:13.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He accepted unreasonable orders from Daimon Industries with a smile, since they had been trading partners for ages.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.75,0:20:19.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, with just one mistake, our transactions with Daimon Industries ceased...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.59,0:20:22.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the factory went bankrupt.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.05,0:20:28.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Daimon Industries overcame their financial difficulty by cutting off my father's factory.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.14,0:20:36.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As if to deal the final blow to my father, Genichiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} stole our family heirloom, the armor, from him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.81,0:20:44.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He sold that armor to raise money to pay his employees.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.82,0:20:51.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He couldn't do anything for his workers, and he had lost a big part of our family's history.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.95,0:20:55.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He blamed himself for it all, and committed suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.71,0:20:59.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While I was working in Tokyo...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.96,0:21:05.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I changed my name and began to live here so that I could absolve my father of his regret...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.93,0:21:11.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And so that I could have my revenge on the anniversary of my father's death.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.52,0:21:13.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hatsuho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}..
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.39,0:21:19.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you think your father would be happy with your revenge?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.94,0:21:23.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you think he'd praise you and say "you did well"?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.99,0:21:25.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hatsuho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}..
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.57,0:21:29.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one who wore the armor wasn't Hidetomo's spirit...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.33,0:21:34.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was your own heart that bore the armor.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.37,0:21:39.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A cold armor called revenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.84,0:23:11.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.30,0:23:13.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.43,0:23:18.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you okay, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.39,0:23:23.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The mark that I left from falling was erased by yours!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.44,0:23:28.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is just like the armor's footprints from before, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.15,0:23:29.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.74,0:23:31.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.78,0:23:32.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean by that?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.95,0:23:35.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What do I mean..
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.66,0:23:37.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, look!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.33,0:23:38.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Get back here, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.66,0:23:40.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.12,0:23:44.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It means you're big and heavy... I guess
